Talita van der Heever says child kidnappers usually have a well laid-out plan when deciding on their victims, and it is seldom a random act. Van der Heever, who gives talks on a life spent in the sex trade, says she has researched the issue of human trafficking and tells parents on what to look out for. According to Van der Heever, social media plays a huge role in human trafficking these days as traffickers are able to pose as ordinary people to get girls to trust them. Her tips include: “This (kidnapping) can happen to anybody,” she said.